==English==
===Etymology===
From [[w:Latin|Latin]][[Category:Latin derivations]] nil, a contraction of [[nihil]], [[nihilum]] (meaning ''nothing''). See [[nihilism]].
===Noun===
'''nil'''

#[[Nothing]].
#:''What are the chances of success?  Nil.''
#[[Zero]] (used especially in the [[soccer]] scores).
#:''Arsenal beat Manchester United two nil.''

===Adjective===
'''nil'''

#No, not any.

